cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the optimization of resource allocation and scheduling in a wireless network, specifically LTE/WiFi aggregation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely category. The use of simulation results and performance evaluation suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category. The paper also deals with quality-of-service (QoS) and resource allocation, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with security challenges in wireless networks, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a possible category.
